crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a backdoor trojan. It gathers system information and proxy settings from both Internet Explorer (registry) and Firefox (parsing 'prefs.js') to establish C2 communication. It then beacons to a C2 server using a distinctive URL pattern, '/%x/ketwer90o/%02d%02d%02d%02d.html', and a hardcoded User-Agent 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Win32)'. The malware is capable of executing arbitrary commands via 'cmd.exe /c' and dynamically loading/executing DLLs, indicating a remote shell functionality.
